1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,225
In survivors, myocarditis can progress to

2
00:00:03,225 --> 00:00:06,450
dilated cardiomyopathy with persistent left ventricular

3
00:00:06,450 --> 00:00:06,987
dysfunction.

4
00:00:06,987 --> 00:00:10,213
Myocardial scar tissue impairs contractility and

5
00:00:10,213 --> 00:00:12,362
creates an arrhythmogenic substrate.

6
00:00:12,362 --> 00:00:15,587
Chronic heart failure, recurrent arrhythmias, and

7
00:00:15,587 --> 00:00:18,813
thromboembolic complications including stroke are documented

8
00:00:18,813 --> 00:00:19,887
long-term consequences.

9
00:00:19,887 --> 00:00:23,113
However, most patients experience complete recovery

10
00:00:23,113 --> 00:00:24,725
with appropriate management.

11
00:00:24,725 --> 00:00:27,950
Long-term follow-up with serial imaging and

12
00:00:27,950 --> 00:00:31,175
risk stratification is essential for those

13
00:00:31,175 --> 00:00:34,400
with fulminant presentations or persistent dysfunction.
